    "is_good_patch": true,
    "synth_pr": "\n## Title: Fix config_libconfig_end() to properly reset libconfig structures\n\n### Summary\nThe `config_libconfig_end()` function in the configuration module was not properly resetting libconfig structures after calling `config_destroy()`. This caused undefined behavior when the config module was re-initialized after being ended, as the config_t structures were left in an invalid state.\n\nThe issue manifested as segmentation faults or incorrect configuration parsing when attempting to reload configuration files after the first initialization->end->re-initialization cycle.\n\nThe fix ensures that after calling `config_destroy()`, the config structures are zeroed out to a clean state using `memset()`, making them safe for re-initialization.\n\n### Changes\n- `common/config/libconfig/config_libconfig.c`: Added `memset()` calls after `config_destroy()` to reset config structures to a clean state\n- `common/config/libconfig/config_libconfig.c`: Added proper comments explaining the reset operations\n\n"
}